cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.ST, cs.IT

The paper deals with machine learning algorithms for linear regression in a budgeted learning setting, where the learner can only observe a small subset of the attributes of each training example. This falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and can also be classified under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it deals with developing efficient algorithms for learning. The paper also involves statistical techniques for estimation and analysis, which can be classified under data science (cs.DS) and statistics (cs.ST). Finally, the paper involves information theory (cs.IT) in the form of analyzing the information content of the observed attributes.
